23  package se.jguru.nazgul.core.cache.impl.inmemory;
24  
25  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.algorithms.api.Validate;
26  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.cache.api.Cache;
27  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.cache.api.CacheListener;
28  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.cache.api.transaction.TransactedAction;
29  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.clustering.api.AbstractSwiftClusterable;
30  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.clustering.api.IdGenerator;
31  import se.jguru.nazgul.core.clustering.api.UUIDGenerator;
32  
33  import javax.validation.constraints.Min;
34  import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;
35  import javax.validation.constraints.Size;
36  import java.io.IOException;
37  import java.io.ObjectInput;
38  import java.io.ObjectOutput;
39  import java.io.Serializable;
40  import java.util.ArrayList;
41  import java.util.Collections;
42  import java.util.HashSet;
43  import java.util.Iterator;
44  import java.util.List;
45  import java.util.Set;
46  import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;
47  import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap;
48  import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;
49  import java.util.concurrent.Executors;
50  
51  /**
52   * Abstract Map-backed implementation of the Cache interface.
53   *
54   * @author <a href="mailto:lj@jguru.se">Lennart J&ouml;relid</a>, jGuru Europe AB
55   */
56  public class InMemoryMapCache extends AbstractSwiftClusterable implements Cache<String, Serializable> {
57  
58      // Internal state
59      private long timeoutMillis;
60      private ConcurrentMap<String, Serializable> cache;
61      private ConcurrentMap<String, CacheListener<String, Serializable>> listeners;
62      private boolean fakeTransactions;
63      private String threadPoolPrefix;
64      private int numEventListenerThreads;
65  
66      private transient ExecutorService listenerThreadService;
67  
68      /**
69       * Default convenience constructor, using an UUIDGenerator, 20 minutes timeout,
70       * empty ConcurrentHashMaps for cache and listener maps, 15 threads in the pool
71       * and not faking transactedActions.
72       */
73      public InMemoryMapCache() {
74  
75          this(UUIDGenerator.getInstance(), 20 * 60 * 60L,
76                  new ConcurrentHashMap<String, Serializable>(),
77                  new ConcurrentHashMap<String, CacheListener<String, Serializable>>(),
78                  15,
79                  false);
80      }
81  
82      /**
83       * Creates a new AbstractIdentifiable and assigns the internal ID state.
84       *
85       * @param idGenerator      The ID generator used to acquire a cluster-unique
86       *                         identifier for this AbstractClusterable instance.
87       * @param timeoutMillis    The cache element timeout in milliseconds.
88       *                         A value of zero implies no timeout/autonomous eviction.
89       * @param cache            The map used for caching instances.
90       * @param listeners        The map used for storing cache listeners.
91       * @param fakeTransactions if {@code true}, this InMemoryMapCache does not throw an UnsupportedOperationException
92       *                         when requested to perform transacted actions.
93       */
94      public InMemoryMapCache(final IdGenerator idGenerator,
95                              @Min(value = 1) final long timeoutMillis,
96                              @NotNull final ConcurrentMap<String, Serializable> cache,
97                              @NotNull final ConcurrentMap<String, CacheListener<String, Serializable>> listeners,
98                              final int numEventListenerThreads,
99                              final boolean fakeTransactions) {
100         super(idGenerator, false);
101 
102         // Check sanity
103         Validate.isTrue(timeoutMillis > 0, "Cannot handle zero or negative milliseconds argument.");
104         Validate.notNull(cache, "cache");
105         Validate.notNull(listeners, "listeners");
106 
107         // Assign internal state
108         this.timeoutMillis = timeoutMillis;
109         this.cache = cache;
110         this.listeners = listeners;
111         this.numEventListenerThreads = numEventListenerThreads;
112         this.threadPoolPrefix = "InMemoryCacheListener-(" + hashCode() + ")";
113         listenerThreadService = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(
114                 numEventListenerThreads, new NamedSequenceThreadFactory(threadPoolPrefix));
115         this.fakeTransactions = fakeTransactions;
116     }
117 
118     /**
119      * {@inheritDoc}
120      */
121     @Override
122     public Serializable remove(final String key) {
123 
124         // Remove the value
125         final Serializable oldValue = cache.remove(key);
126 
127         // Notify any listeners
128         if (!listeners.isEmpty()) {
129 
130             final Set<CacheListener<String, Serializable>> localListeners
131                     = new HashSet<CacheListener<String, Serializable>>(listeners.values());
132 
133             listenerThreadService.execute(
134                     new CacheListenerNotificationWorker(localListeners, CacheEventType.REMOVE, key, oldValue, null));
135         }
136 
137         // All done.
138         return oldValue;
139     }
140 
141     /**
142      * {@inheritDoc}
143      */
144     @Override
145     public Serializable put(final String key, final Serializable value) {
146 
147         // Put the value in the cache
148         final Serializable oldValue = cache.put(key, value);
149 
150         // Notify any listeners
151         if (!listeners.isEmpty()) {
152 
153             final Set<CacheListener<String, Serializable>> localListeners
154                     = new HashSet<CacheListener<String, Serializable>>(listeners.values());
155             final CacheEventType cacheEventType = oldValue == null ? CacheEventType.PUT : CacheEventType.UPDATE;
156 
157             listenerThreadService.execute(
158                     new CacheListenerNotificationWorker(localListeners, cacheEventType, key, oldValue, value));
159         }
160 
161         // All done.
162         return oldValue;
163     }
164 
165     /**
166      * {@inheritDoc}
167      */
168     @Override
169     public Serializable get(final String key) {
170         return cache.get(key);
171     }
172 
173     /**
174      * {@inheritDoc}
175      */
176     @Override
177     public boolean containsKey(final String key) {
178         return cache.containsKey(key);
179     }
180 
181     /**
182      * Returns an iterator to a readonly version of the cache map.
183      *
184      * @return an Iterator to a readonly version of the cache map.
185      */
186     @Override
187     public Iterator<String> iterator() {
188         return Collections.unmodifiableMap(cache).keySet().iterator();
189     }
190 
191     /**
192      * {@inheritDoc}
193      */
194     @Override
195     public boolean addListener(final CacheListener<String, Serializable> listener) {
196         final CacheListener<String, Serializable> putListener
197                 = listeners.putIfAbsent(listener.getClusterId(), listener);
198         return putListener == listener;
199     }
200 
201     /**
202      * Retrieves an unmodifiable list of all listener IDs.
203      * {@inheritDoc}
204      */
205     @Override
206     public List<String> getListenerIds() {
207         return Collections.unmodifiableList(new ArrayList<String>(listeners.keySet()));
208     }
209 
210     /**
211      * {@inheritDoc}
212      */
213     @Override
214     public void removeListener(final String key) {
215         listeners.remove(key);
216     }
217 
218     /**
219      * {@inheritDoc}
220      */
221     @Override
222     protected void performWriteExternal(final ObjectOutput out) throws IOException {
223 
224         // Write out state
225         out.writeLong(timeoutMillis);
226         out.writeBoolean(fakeTransactions);
227         out.writeInt(numEventListenerThreads);
228         out.writeUTF(threadPoolPrefix);
229         out.writeObject(listeners);
230         out.writeObject(cache);
231     }
232 
233     /**
234      * {@inheritDoc}
235      */
236     @Override
237     protected void performReadExternal(final ObjectInput in) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {
238 
239         // Read in state
240         timeoutMillis = in.readLong();
241         fakeTransactions = in.readBoolean();
242         numEventListenerThreads = in.readInt();
243         threadPoolPrefix = in.readUTF();
244         listeners = (ConcurrentMap<String, CacheListener<String, Serializable>>) in.readObject();
245         cache = (ConcurrentMap<String, Serializable>) in.readObject();
246 
247         // Re-create the (transient) ExecutorService
248         this.listenerThreadService = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(
249                 numEventListenerThreads, new NamedSequenceThreadFactory(threadPoolPrefix));
250     }
251 
252     /**
253      * Acquires a Transactional context from this Cache, and Executes the
254      * TransactedAction::doInTransaction method within it.
255      *
256      * @param action The TransactedAction to be executed within a Cache Transactional context.
257      * @throws UnsupportedOperationException if the underlying Cache implementation does not
258      *                                       support Transactions.
259      */
260     @Override
261     public void performTransactedAction(final TransactedAction action) throws UnsupportedOperationException {
262 
263         if (fakeTransactions) {
264             action.doInTransaction();
265         } else {
266             throw new UnsupportedOperationException("InMemoryMapCaches do not support transactions. Use "
267                     + "the fakeTransactions initialization parameter to simulate transacted behaviour.");
268         }
269     }
270 
271     //
272     // Helpers
273     //
274 
275     class CacheListenerNotificationWorker implements Runnable {
276 
277         // Internal state
278         private Set<CacheListener<String, Serializable>> listeners;
279         private CacheEventType event;
280         private String key;
281         private Serializable oldValue;
282         private Serializable newValue;
283 
284         /**
285          * Creates a CacheListenerNotificationWorker runnable which is used by the ExecutorService to perform
286          * asynchronous callbacks to cache listeners.
287          *
288          * @param listeners The set of listeners which should be notified.
289          * @param event     The event type generated.
290          * @param key       The cache key.
291          * @param oldValue  The old value of the cache entry.
292          * @param newValue  The new value of the cache entry.
293          */
294         CacheListenerNotificationWorker(
295                 @NotNull @Size(min = 1) final Set<CacheListener<String, Serializable>> listeners,
296                 @NotNull final CacheEventType event,
297                 @NotNull final String key,
298                 final Serializable oldValue,
299                 final Serializable newValue) {
300 
301             super();
302 
303             // Check sanity
304             Validate.notNull(event, "event");
305             Validate.notEmpty(listeners, "listeners");
306             Validate.notEmpty(key, "key");
307 
308             // Assign internal state
309             this.listeners = listeners;
310             this.event = event;
311             this.key = key;
312             this.oldValue = oldValue;
313             this.newValue = newValue;
314         }
315 
316         /**
317          * {@inheritDoc}
318          */
319         @Override
320         @SuppressWarnings("all")
321         public void run() {
322 
323             for (CacheListener<String, Serializable> current : listeners) {
324 
325                 switch (event) {
326 
327                     case PUT:
328                         current.onPut(key, newValue);
329                         break;
330 
331                     case UPDATE:
332                         current.onUpdate(key, newValue, oldValue);
333                         break;
334 
335                     case REMOVE:
336                         current.onRemove(key, oldValue);
337                         break;
338 
339                     case CLEAR:
340                         current.onClear();
341                         break;
342 
343                     case AUTONOMOUS_EVICT:
344                         current.onAutonomousEvict(key, newValue);
345                         break;
346 
347                     case AUTONOMOUS_LOAD:
348                         current.onAutonomousLoad(key, newValue);
349                         break;
350 
351                     default:
352                         throw new IllegalStateException("Could not identify cache event [" + event + "]");
353                 }
354             }
355         }
356     }
357 }
